1. Global Styles & Theme
   Color Palette:

Primary Blue: #0052cc (Buttons, icons, accents)

Background: #f8fafc (Light grey/white)

Text: #0f172a (Deep navy/black)

Footer Background: #0f172a

Typography: Use a clean Sans-Serif font like Inter, Roboto, or Public Sans.

Spacing: Use consistent padding (e.g., py-20 for sections) and large border radii (rounded-2xl) for the feature cards.

2. Component Architecture
   Section A: Navigation & Hero (Image 1)
   Navbar: Sticky header with Logo (left), Links (center), and "Sign In" button (right).

Hero Layout: Two-column grid (60/40 split).

Left: H1 Heading ("The Card That Speaks..."), subtext, and a flex container for two CTA buttons.

Right: Floating 3D mockup of the BiosCard over a smartphone.

Section B: How It Works (Image 2)
Container: Centered text heading.

The Three-Step Grid: A 3-column grid featuring white cards with:

Large blue circular icons.

Bolded step numbers (1, 2, 3).

Short descriptive text.

Section C: Why Choose Bios? (Image 3)
Grid: 2x2 Bento-style grid.

Card Design: \* Top-left aligned blue square icons.

H3 Title.

Body text in a muted grey/navy.

Hover Effect: Add a subtle transform: translateY(-5px) and a soft shadow for interactivity.

Section D: Crisis Moments Feature (Image 4)
Layout: Two-column grid (50/50).

Content: \* Left: H2 Title followed by a checklist using custom blue check icons.

Right: High-fidelity smartphone mockup showing the actual emergency interface (UI showing high contrast and red "Allergies" alert).

Section E: Footer & Final CTA (Image 5)
CTA Banner: Full-width primary blue background. Bold white text with two rounded outline/solid buttons.

Footer: Dark background with 4 columns:

Col 1: Logo and tagline.

Cols 2-4: Vertical link lists (Product, For Professionals, Company).

Bottom Bar: Copyright and social media icons (Twitter, LinkedIn, Facebook).
